==German==
===Etymology===
Compound of ''[[aus]]'' and ''[[weisen]]''
===Verb===
'''ausweisen''' (''separable'' aus + weisen, ''preterite'' wies aus, ''participle'' ausgewiesen, ''auxiliary verb'' [[haben]])

# to [[expel]]
# (''financial'') [[show]], [[display]]
# (''with reflexive pronoun'') to prove one's identity

===Usage===
* Er konnte sich ausweisen - He could prove his identity